quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
  10,54,"And if every single self which had committed injustice possessed whatever is in the earth, it would offer it as a ransom. And they hid<a class=""sup""><sup>b </sup></a>their remorse when they saw the punishment, and it was judged between them equitably. And they are not dealt with unjustly."
  10,55,"Undoubtedly, to Allah does belong whatever is in the heavens and the earth. Undoubtedly, the promise of Allah is indeed true, but most of them do not know."
  10,56,"He gives life and causes death, and to Him you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a><span class=""h"">are returned<sup foot_note=""80221"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>."
  10,57,"O mankind, there has come to you an admonition from your Lord and a cure for what lies within the chests and guidance and mercy for the believers."
  10,58,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “In Allah’s grace and in His mercy—in that then, <span class=""h"">let them rejoice; it is better than what they hoard<sup foot_note=""80222"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>.”"
  10,59,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “Have you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>seen the provision Allah has sent down for you, some of which you made unlawful and some lawful?” Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “Did Allah give you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>permission, or do you fabricate lies and attribute them to Allah?”"
  10,60,"And what assumption do those who fabricate lies and attribute them to Allah have about the Day of Resurrection? Most surely, Allah is the Possessor of grace towards mankind, but most of them do not give thanks."
  10,61,"For you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>do not engage in any affair, nor do you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>read any<i class=""s"">(portion) </i>of the Recital{1}, nor do you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>do anything, but We are witnessing over you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>as you undertake it. And not even the weight of an atom in the earth or in the heaven escapes your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord{2}, <span class=""h"">for nothing smaller than this nor larger<sup foot_note=""80225"" class=""qiraat"">3</sup> </span>but is in an evident record{4}.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is Qur’anwhich literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.|2:A grammatical shift from 1st person to 3rd person.|4:Literally ‘scripture’.
